<TEXT>
north korea is preparing to stage the largest 
international gathering ever in that isolated country a youth 
festival with an antiimperialist theme 
about 30000 people from more than 170 countries are expected 
for the 13th world festival of youth and students on july 18 in 
pyongyang said so man sul chairman of a preparatory committee for 
the pronorth korean general association of korean residents in 
japan 
about 20000 people from 157 countries attended the last 
festival in moscow in 1985 so said 
north korea has not held a major international event since the 
35th world table tennis championships in 1979 which brought 900 
players from 85 countries to pyongyang 
north korea had demanded to be a cohost with seoul of the 1988 
summer olympics the international olympic committee offered to let 
it stage several of the olympic events but the offer fell short of 
north koreas demands and it boycotted the games 
so said the youth festival would be the largest international 
gathering ever held in the north korean capital since korea was 
divided at the end of world war ii 
the festivals theme is antiimperialist solidarity and 
peace and will include representatives from the united states 
japan and western europe 
the festival first held in prague in 1947 is a major 
political cultural and sports event involving mostly communist and 
third world nations previous hosts have included budapest east 
berlin bucharest warsaw vienna helsinki sofia and havana 
asked about prospects for south koreas participation so said 
we arent so optimistic 
north korea has invited south korean radical students to attend 
in letters sent through the south korean government since april 
however south korea has refused to accept further north korean 
letters meant for radical student groups and dissidents 
the policy change followed an unauthorized trip to north korea 
by a south korean dissident the rev moon ikhwan for talks on 
national unification 
moon was arrested on his return to south korea on april 13 on 
charges of violating a law requiring all south koreans to obtain 
government permission to visit north korea the communist nation 
suspended all dialogue with south korea to protest moons arrest 
so said sports events at the festival would include the 
marathon soccer basketball volleyball table tennis gymnastics 
swimming and diving 
all facilities for the festival have been completed in and 
around the capital of pyongyang he added including hotels 
stadiums and theaters 
north korean officials have been quoted by foreign media as 
saying about 4 billion was spent on the festival so far 
