the lessons we have drawn have important applicability to 
developments in nicaragua 
our experience is that the quality and intention of an 
electoral law is but one element of the critical determinants of 
whether an election will be free and fair he testified the 
other two points of analysis are the caliber and organization of 
the opposition and the overall organization of government 
there are disturbing parallels too frequent to be considered 
accidental between these three elements in the cases of nicaragua 
and panama he said 
he said he had concluded that sufficient freedom of 
organization expression and activity does not currently exist to 
