view that such backward practices remain the norm in some 
conference on security and cooperation in europe countries he 
said referring to the four nations 
when these countries were justly criticized bauer said 
we were treated to the same tired old arguments that criticism 
was internal interference or deliberately confrontational 
the security conference ended in january in vienna with 
agreements committing the 35 signatories to improve the flow of 
information and improve working conditions for journalists 
czechoslovakian chief delegate dusan spacil the only one of the 
four to speak thursday said in his concluding statement that 
confrontation or bias or disinformation is 
counterproductive 
