the most controversial step bush announced the dispatch of 2000 
or more us combat troops 
noriega may be concerned that the troops have a more aggressive 
purpose in mind than the stated one of protecting american lives 
it is not unusual for a strong nation to try to achieve political 
goals by projecting military power without actually using it 
bush backed away from a more pugnacious military response out of 
concern that it could provoke antiamerican uprisings in the 
hemisphere that approach might have succeeded in ousting noriega 
but the diplomatic costs would have been exorbitant 
slapping a trade embargo on panama would have made the economy 
there scream but the impact would have been felt for years to come 
