the united states and soviet union agreed thursday 
to cooperate in pollution emergencies in northern waters like the 
oil spill that has fouled alaskas coastline 
secretary of state james a baker iii and soviet foreign 
minister eduard a shevardnadze signed the accord on the last day 
of bakers twoday visit to moscow it pledges superpower 
cooperation in combating spills of oil and other pollutants in the 
bering and chukchi seas between alaska and siberia 
the news agency tass said the agreement provides for the 
development of a joint plan of drastic measures by the 
superpowers in the event of a spill each country is required to 
notify the other immediately of a pollution emergency and us and 
soviet officials will hold joint exercises on how to fight ocean 
pollution tass said 
the signing of the agreement is a major step toward developing 
sovietamerican cooperation in dealing with the consequences of 
ecological disaster at sea oleg khalimonov an official in the 
soviet merchant marine ministry told tass 
khalimonov was quoted as saying the cooperation will allow 
specialists to define within hours the scope of an accident map 
out joint measures to overcome its consequences and get down 
immediately to their implementation earlier such procedures took 
days and sometimes whole weeks 
tass said the cooperation envisaged by the agreement began to 
function even before baker and shevardnadze signed the formal 
document a soviet ship designed to skim the surface of the sea was 
