<TEXT>
a fire that gutted a breeding center 
housing about 500000 laboratory mice will cause a worldwide 
disruption of laboratories researching aids cancer and other 
diseases officials said thursday 
kenneth paigen the incoming director of jackson laboratory 
pledged to get back up as fast as we possibly can as salvage 
teams searched for living mice within the research centers 
stillsmoldering animal production facility 
the laboratory which distributes about 2 million mice annually 
to researchers is the worlds leading nonprofit supplier and 
developer of mutant mice bred in hundreds of genetically identical 
strains 
about a halfmillion mice would be in the facility on any given 
day officials said but there was no estimate of how many or what 
types might have survived 
paigen said the center had saved its foundation stocks of 
specially bred mice but warned that supply disruptions would hamper 
researchers who need the mice to investigate cancer aids and other 
human diseases 
thousands of labs literally all over the world depend on us 
for supplies of mice genetically defined animals paigen said 
i think its safe to say we have some of everything but how 
much we have of anything is not clear right now said philip 
standel director of animal production the laboratory located two 
miles outside the picturesque resort village of bar harbor housed 
about 1000 strains of mice many of them rare 
the impact is going to be terrific really detrimental said 
salome waelsch a professor of molecular genetics at the albert 
einstein college of medicine in new york 
there is no way of restoring this facility by just importing 
mice from elsewhere said waelsch a member of the national 
academy of science 
