one suit was filed by alan r kahn trustee for the estate of 
samuel adason jaffe which holds 700 occidental shares the other 
by joseph sullivan and alan i brody who describe themselves as 
occidental shareholders without detailing their holdings 
they seek injunctions that among other things would bar 
further occidental support of the museum including rentfree use 
of company buildings cancel compensation to hammer and require an 
accounting of any losses the company incurred in connection with 
the museum 
they also allege that proxy material mailed to shareholders for 
the companys upcoming annual meeting was misleading about the 36 
million expenditure for the museum including it as unallocated 
corporate expenses 
the sullivanbrody suit paints a particularly unflattering 
portrait of occidentals chairman and chief executive officer in 
detailing a dispute with the los angeles county museum of art over 
the future of his personal collection said to be worth 250 
million to 400 million 
the collection includes works by dutch flemish german and 
italian masters impressionist works and a codex or book of notes 
and drawings by da vinci 
last year hammer canceled what the museum portrayed as a 
promise to donate his art to the county when museum officials 
rejected conditions including posting a fulllength portrait of the 
industrialist at the entrance to the exhibit 
other conditions unacceptable to the museum according the suit 
that the collection be kept intact forever and displayed under 
hammers name that names of other museum benefactors be removed 
from galleries displaying hammers art that the collection get a 
special curator answerable to a hammer foundation rather than to 
the museum 
the dispute led to hammers plan to build his own museum the 
suit says adding unlike other wealthy collectors dr hammer 
does not plan to build his own museum with his own ample funds 
rather dr hammer is requiring occidental to provide substantially 
all the financial support 
company attorney kauffman disputed at least part of that noting 
the considerable value of the collection hammer intended to 
contribute to the project 
hammer whose 1987 pay was 19 million has held sway over 
occidental since 1957 
based on contacts he made during a postworld war ii medical 
mercy mission in the soviet union he served as unofficial envoy 
for the united states government during the cold war as relations 
have thawed in recent years he has led a parade of american 
businesses into the soviet union setting up joint ventures for 
chemical plants and the like 
hammer who holds a medical degree has used his connections and 
company jet to get american doctors to the scene of various 
disasters including the chernobyl nuclear accident and the 
armenian earthquake 
